public debt sustainability, as well as the ability to have access to financing resources in the post 
disaster conditions. This exercise is combined with the technical assessment of the probability of event 
occurring. If the disaster risk is minor and the risk bearing capacity is high, ex post solutions would be 
more rational for some governments (G20/OECD, 2012) 32 . When the insurance is deemed necessary, governments can get involved in this process in various 
